{"sections":[{"projectFiles":"CF2G-FirstPackage.zip","estimatedTimeInMinutes":20,"kind":"hero","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this tutorial you can learn how to create your first 2D scene using AdaEngine","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Create your first 2D scene","chapter":"Create your first 2D game project.","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 14.3 or later"},{"tasks":[{"anchor":"Intro","stepsSection":[],"title":"Intro","contentSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the first 2D scene we will try to repeat this example. We’ll look at adding a scene and a camera.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, we’ll learn how to add sprites and movement systems."}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","media":"CF2G-3-5.mov"}]},{"stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the previous tutorial we’ve created an app and an empty game scene."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":null,"code":"CF2G-1-1-app.swift"},{"code":"CF2G-1-2-scene.swift","runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"caption":[],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s create a game scene. To do this, let’s create a file named ","type":"text"},{"code":"FirstScene.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and import AdaEngine. After that, create a class named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FirstScene"},{"type":"text","text":" and add a method named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sceneDidMove(to view: SceneView)"},{"text":" where we will setup entities to our scene.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Great! Now we can create and return our game scene instance to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GameAppScene"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"code":"CF2G-1-4-app.swift","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GameAppScene"},{"text":" will automatically create a game window with your scene.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"}],"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the first time, we should create base files to launch our application","type":"text"}]}]}],"title":"Create an app","anchor":"Create-an-app"},{"stepsSection":[{"code":"CF2G-2-1-camera.swift","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s create our 2D camera. Create an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrthographicCamera"},{"type":"text","text":" entity and add this entity to the scene using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"addEntity"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"media":null,"caption":[],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now let’s fill the camera background with sky blue color.","type":"text"}]}],"code":"CF2G-2-2-camera.swift","runtimePreview":"CF2G-2-1.png"}],"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"AdaEngine used Entity Component System paradigm where all game objects are called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Entity"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Entities are objects that store user or engine data like position, scale, mesh instance, audio etc. This data is called components and they should inherit from ","type":"text"},{"code":"Component","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Camera"},{"type":"text","text":" is a component where all entities will render. AdaEngine supports rendering to the texture or to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Window"},{"type":"text","text":". We recommend you to use engine entities "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OrthographicCamera"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PerspectiveCamera"},{"type":"text","text":", because the engine provides additional components for rendering and audio capabilities."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"fullWidth"}],"anchor":"Create-a-main-camera","title":"Create a main camera."},{"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now we can create our first custom sprite."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"stepsSection":[{"type":"step","media":"CF2G-3-1.png","runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"code":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First we should create an assets folder where we will store our game assets, like sprite sheets, sounds, shaders, etc. Let’s create a folder named ","type":"text"},{"code":"Assets","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and add any sprite sheets you want, we will use this next sprite sheet."}]}]},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can download this texture using right click on image from right and save it to the downloads folder."}]}],"code":null,"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":"CF2G-3-2.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In the end we should have this file structure in our project. AdaEngine doesn’t use xcassets and","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a player entity and then add it to the scene. Player entity will store our sprite component and other player data."}]}],"code":"CF2G-3-1-sprite.swift","type":"step","caption":[]},{"type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"code":"CF2G-3-2-sprite.swift","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s create an image from a file using a special resource manager object. "},{"code":"ResourceManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" manages and cache game and engine resources. In our case we should load an image from a file named "},{"code":"characters_packed.png","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bundle.main"},{"type":"text","text":" as a search path."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To split the sprite sheet image to sprites we can use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"TextureAtlas","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object. This object gets an image, sprite size and margin between sprites if needed. In our case we have a margin between sprites 4xp horizontally and 1px vertically and sprite size 20px width and 23px height."}]}],"type":"step","code":"CF2G-3-3-sprite.swift","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"media":null},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a new sprite component to entity components using the special "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+="},{"text":" operator. As you can see we use subscripts in our TextureAtlas instance where 7 is the number of columns in our sprite sheet and 1 is the number of rows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"CF2G-3-4-sprite.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now we can add our sprite to the player entity using special ","type":"text"},{"code":"SpriteComponent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". These components are efficient for rendering, because they use a special batching system and require less drawing calls.","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"runtimePreview":"CF2G-3-3.png","type":"step"},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default "},{"code":"Entity","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Transform"},{"text":" component when initialized.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And finally let’s set the scale for our sprite. Create a special "},{"code":"Transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" component with scale equals 0.19. ","type":"text"},{"code":"Vector3.init(_ scalar: Float)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" creates a vector with x, y, z components equals scalar value."}]}],"runtimePreview":"CF2G-3-4.png","media":null,"code":"CF2G-3-5-sprite.swift"}],"title":"First sprite","anchor":"First-sprite"},{"title":"Make it move","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"code":"CF2G-4-1-player.swift","caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First we should create a special tag component named ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PlayerComponent"},{"text":". This component we will use in the near future and indicates for us that this entity is a player.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step"},{"media":null,"caption":[],"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a new system named ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MovementSystem"},{"type":"text","text":". This system will listen to user inputs and move our player component on the screen. System interface required "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(scene:)"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update(context:)"},{"text":" methods.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"CF2G-4-2-player.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"code":"CF2G-4-3-player.swift","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a new system to our game scene. Our system will be created once the game scene will be active and present on the screen.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","media":null},{"code":"CF2G-4-4-player.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MovementSystem"},{"text":" add a static property named ","type":"text"},{"code":"playerQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and set a special "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntityQuery"},{"text":" object. This object will request a scene world with a special query and returns entities that conform to your predicate. In our case we will require two components in entity ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PlayerComponent"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Transform"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Also add a property named ","type":"text"},{"code":"speed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which will store our player speed value."}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":null},{"code":"CF2G-4-5-player.swift","media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now we can make our first request to the scene using the special scene method "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"performQuery"},{"type":"text","text":". This method will return a sequence of entities that conforms to our query."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the next query to the update method."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s iterate over all founded entities using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forEach"},{"type":"text","text":" loop and get the "},{"code":"Transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component."}]}],"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":null,"code":"CF2G-4-6-player.swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We want to update our player position so that we should listen to keyboard inputs and if some key is pressed, we should change player transform."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"step","caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Get ","type":"text"},{"code":"Transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component from entity using "},{"code":"components","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property from entity. You can do this using subscript."}]}],"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"code":"CF2G-4-6-player.swift"},{"code":"CF2G-4-7-player.swift","media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"if"},{"type":"text","text":" condition where we will listen to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"w"},{"type":"text","text":" key. If the key is pressed, then add multiplication speed by delta time. We do this for smooth transition between frames."}]}],"caption":[],"type":"step"},{"media":null,"code":"CF2G-4-8-player.swift","caption":[],"type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now we should set a new, modified transform to our entity, to apply a new transform in the scene.","type":"text"}]}]},{"runtimePreview":"CF2G-3-5.mov","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the app and try to move your player"}]}],"media":null,"code":"CF2G-4-9-player.swift","type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally, add the same logic for other keys - "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"s","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"anchor":"Make-it-move","contentSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We did a lot of work, but our scene looks very simple. We should add more life for our player entity. All game logic we describe in special objects named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"System"},{"type":"text","text":". System is a unit that executes each game loop and manipulates entities and their data. We will use one to add life for our player."}]}],"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}]}],"kind":"tasks"},{"abstract":[{"text":"In this tutorial, you will learn how to add a player component that you can control and how to add text and various labels to your game s